{{Refimprove|date=September 2015}} '''Ibimirim''' is a city in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. The population in 2009, according with [[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|IBGE]] was 29.018 inhabitants and the total area is 2033.59&nbsp;km². [[File:Bandeira de Ibimirim.jpg|thumb|right|160px|City Flag]]
==Geography== * State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Sertão]] Pernambucano * Boundaries - [[Custódia]] and [[Sertânia]] ('''N'''); [[Inajá, Pernambuco|Inajá]] and [[Manari, Pernambuco|Manari]] ('''S'''); [[Tupanatinga]] ('''E'''); [[Floresta, Pernambuco|Floresta]] ('''W'''). * Area - 2033.59&nbsp;km² * Elevation - 401 m * Hidrography - [[Moxotó River]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] [[hiperxerófila]] * Clima - [[semi arid]] - ([[Sertão]]) hot * Annual average temperature - 24.7 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 331.6&nbsp;km
==Economy== The main economic activities in '''Ibimirim''' are based in commerce and [[agribusiness]], especially creation of [[goat]]s, [[sheep]], [[pigs]]s, [[cattle]], [[donkey]]s, [[horse]]s, [[chicken]]s; and plantations of [[tomato]]es, [[bean]]s, [[mango]]es and [[banana]]s.
